ttps://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-80x43.png 80w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-150x80.png 150w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-469x250.png 469w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-650x347.png 650w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-300x160.png 300w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-160x85.png 160w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" srcset=\"https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature.png 750w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-80x43.png 80w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-150x80.png 150w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-469x250.png 469w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-650x347.png 650w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-300x160.png 300w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-160x85.png 160w\" style=\"vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; padding: 0px; outline: 0px; background: transparent; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); line-height: 1.56; letter-spacing: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto; clear: both; display: block; position: sticky; margin-bottom: 0px !important;\"></picture></div><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">Here’s a really good reason why you need an app landing page:</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">Have you looked at your iPhone’s App Store lately? How about Google Play?</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">I’ve seen&nbsp;<em style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 0.94444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6;\">landfills</em>&nbsp;with better curation.</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">With&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/276623/number-of-apps-available-in-leading-app-stores/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">more than two million apps</a>&nbsp;available on each store, people have a much better chance of finding&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.spey.com/2017/04/05/the-odds-of-finding-a-pearl/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">a pearl in an oyster</a>&nbsp;than randomly stumbling upon your app.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">No matter how appealing it is—no matter how entertaining or even life-changing—most people won’t discover it without a robust marketing campaign.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">(And, to paraphrase&nbsp;<a href=\"https://contently.com/2018/12/14/viral-video-strategy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Contently’s Bradley Little</a>, going viral is&nbsp;<em style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 0.94444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6;\">not</em>&nbsp;a strategy.)</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">The first step in marketing your iPhone or Android app is finding the right channels to promote it. Using Google Ads’ Universal App Campaigns (UAC) is a strong starting point, but many marketers get extra mileage from traditional PPC campaign, social media marketing, app cross-promotion, or even email blasts to newsletter subscribers.</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">In these cases, you’ll need a stellar landing page to overcome that hesitance we all feel about installing yet another piece of software onto our phones. For this reason,&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">ensuring a buttery-smooth post-click experience is fundamental to the app marketer’s toolbox</span>.</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">Hence this post. These are some of the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">best app landing page examples</span>&nbsp;out there, all of ’em built with Unbounce. We want to highlight how you can create a page to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.appypie.com/how-to-promote-your-mobile-app\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">promote your own mobile app</a>&nbsp;and, as importantly, why a well-designed landing page can make all the difference. Along the way, we’ll throw in our two cents about what sets them apart.</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">So&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unbounce.com/landing-page-examples/app-landing-pages/#best\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">hop right into the examples below</a>, or keep reading for a handful of best practices to get you started.</p><h2 style=\"margin: 30px auto 15px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-family: &quot;Barlow Semi Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 1.44444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); line-height: 1.3; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">How to build mobile app landing pages</h2><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">If you’ve created a landing page for any ol’ purpose, you may have encountered some of this advice before. But it’s worth revisiting in the context of app marketing since some elements gain increased importance when you’re hoping to score some downloads. Let’s get started:</p><ol style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 15px auto 30px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px 0px 0px 45px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\"><li style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; position: sticky;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">Establish your conversion goal first.</span>&nbsp;As you’ll see from the examples below, an app landing page can be a lot of things. It can be a simple download page with links directly to the Android and iOS app stores. Or you might want your customers to subscribe to your service first.&nbsp;<em style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6;\">Or</em>&nbsp;they might need to purchase a physical product for the app to work. Regardless, your conversion goal will have a significant impact on your calls-to-action, your copy, and even your design. So start there.</li><li style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; position: sticky;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">Start with mobile.</span>&nbsp;If you’re like me, you default to desktop when building a new landing page. (Our builder kinda sorta encourages it, to be fair.) But since apps are designed primarily for phones, it&nbsp;<em style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6;\">usually</em>&nbsp;makes sense to create your mobile version first. That way, you’ll better set yourself up for those visitors who’re most likely to download your app.</li><li style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; position: sticky;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">Keep their attention.</span>&nbsp;This is true of all landing pages, but app pages that encourage a direct download in particular benefit from a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unbounce.com/conversion-centered-design/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(246, 146, 30); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; outline: none; outline-offset: -2px; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">1:1 attention ratio</a>. So don’t give ’em the world. Instead, hit your visitors with the essential information they need to convert.</li><li style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; position: sticky;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">Show the device.</span>&nbsp;Ideally, you want to show your app running on a device that’s as similar as possible to what customers are using. Sometimes that’s an iPhone. Sometimes it’s an Android phone. It’ll differ depending on use cases, the campaign you’re running, and the kinds of customers you court.</li><li style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; position: sticky;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">And stay fast!</span>&nbsp;It can be tempting to take a kitchen-sink approach to your app landing page, especially if you have a lot of features to show off. But generally a slow post-click experience (think, four seconds or more) is going to generate a ton of frustration and decrease your conversions. For this reason, consider using&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unbounce.com/product/features/amp-landing-pages/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">the AMP-framework</a>&nbsp;to create lightning-fast pages.</li></ol></div>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-26 20:08:04', '2022-04-26 20:08:04'),
(17, 'custom_page', 'Help Center', 'help-center', '<div class=\"banner banner-default block-bg-image\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; background-size: cover; z-index: 0; position: relative; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><div class=\"banner-default__content banner-default__content--align-center\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; padding: 180px 2.5rem 60px; width: 1160px; max-width: 1160px; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; -webkit-box-orient: horizontal; -webkit-box-direction: normal; flex-direction: row; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><div class=\"fullwidth\" id=\"glossarytitle\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; max-width: 660px; margin: 0px auto;\"><h1 class=\"banner-default__title\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-weight: 600; font-stretch: normal; color: inherit; width: 660px; text-align: center; letter-spacing: 0px !important; font-size: 50px !important; line-height: 1.1em !important;\">What is a Help Center?</h1></div></div></div><main class=\"main-content\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-family: Lato, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;\"><div class=\"tmpl-glossary\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><section class=\"block-container\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; z-index: 0; position: relative;\"><div class=\"block-inner\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; padding: 9rem 0px;\"><div class=\"row align-center\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; max-width: 1160px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; -webkit-box-orient: horizontal; -webkit-box-direction: normal; flex-direction: row; -webkit-box-pack: center; justify-content: center; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><div class=\"columns small-12 large-10 wysiwyg\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; -webkit-box-flex: 0; flex: 0 0 83.3333%; padding-right: 2.5rem; padding-left: 2.5rem; min-width: 0px; max-width: 83.3333%;\"><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">A Help Center is a website where customers can find answers to their questions and solutions to their problems. Designed to resolve many common queries that a brand receives, a Help Center should make it simple for customers to find the answers they’re looking for.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Good Help Centers are well organized and carefully presented, making it easy for customers to navigate the site and find what they’re searching for.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Help Centers should always be easily searchable, providing customers with an accessible version of a brand’s knowledge base that has been created with users in mind. The site will often incorporate FAQs, articles and a good variety of instructions, all of which should be of digestible length.</p><div class=\"wp-block-image\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; margin: 0px;\"><figure class=\"aligncenter\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; margin-right: auto; margin-bottom: 0px; margin-left: auto; clear: both; display: table; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><img width=\"768\" height=\"576\" src=\"https://helpshift.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/HELP_Ticket-deflection-768x576.png\" alt=\"\" class=\"wp-image-5713\" srcset=\"//helpshift.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/HELP_Ticket-deflection-768x576.png 768w, //helpshift.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/HELP_Ticket-deflection-768x576-600x450.png 600w, //helpshift.b-cdn.net/wp-content/uploads/2019/07/HELP_Ticket-deflection-768x576-300x225.png 300w\" sizes=\"(max-width: 768px) 100vw, 768px\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; height: auto; max-width: 100%; display: inline-block; vertical-align: bottom; border-radius: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"></figure></div><h2 id=\"h-what-does-a-help-desk-center-do\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 4.2rem; line-height: 1.22; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; font-weight: 600;\">What Does a Help Desk Center Do?</span></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">A Help Desk Center cuts the costs associated with customer service, while simultaneously improving the customer experience.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Providing customers with the answers to the questions that get asked all the time, a Help Desk Center makes it easier for consumers to access the information they need, without having to contact a member of the customer service team. Common queries can therefore be dealt with quickly, giving customer service teams more time to focus on the complex problems that need their attention.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">With a whole host of resources available to any one that needs them, a Help Desk Center enables brands to improve their offering and optimize the customer journey.</p><h3 id=\"h-why-do-help-centers-matter-in-customer-service\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 3rem; line-height: 1.25; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; font-weight: 600;\">Why Do Help Centers Matter in Customer Service?</span></h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Today’s customers are increasingly tech-savvy and that means that wherever possible, they like to be able to find solutions to queries themselves.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">While dynamic and hands-on customer service is critical to customer experience, so too is the opportunity to get answers to questions quickly. When customers can help themselves to these answers, the customer experience improves considerably. Since many customer service inquiries are routine and repetitive, these are typically the issues that can be handled via a help center, allowing the customer to seek answers independently.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">High-quality help center software can provide a platform for you to give your customers a faster, sharper, sleeker self-service experience on your website and mobile app. Enabling your customers to self-serve with a help center doesn’t just expedite<em style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">&nbsp;their&nbsp;</em>experience, either. It also maximizes ticket deflection and ultimately drives down your support costs.&nbsp;</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">The first step to having a usable and useful help center is to establish a strong, robust knowledge base you can point customers to. Using this platform, will be able to find the answers to a lot of their own questions. When they can’t, bots come into play.</p><h3 id=\"h-who-uses-help-center-software\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 3rem; line-height: 1.25; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Who Uses Help Center Software?</h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">As the technical knowledge of customers improves, so too does the way that they seek customer service help from brands.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Help Center software can be used to make it easier for all customers to find answers to the questions they’re wanting to ask, without having to waste time waiting for a response from a customer service representative. Help Center software is now being used by brands in a wide range of different industries, from technology companies to fashion and beauty brands.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Every organisation has a list of questions its customer service teams are asked time and time again, so why not make it quicker and simpler for customers to find the answers to these questions? With this software, it’s so easy to do exactly that.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Once your new Help Center is up and running, customers can be directed to it whenever they experience a problem or need to ask a question. In the vast majority of cases they’ll find exactly what they’re looking for in a matter of moments.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">If a customer’s query is more complex, they can be directed to contact a member of the customer service team for help. And the opportunities of automation don’t stop there. At this point, bots can be used to prioritise different queries, directing customers to a relevant member of the team who will be able to assist them further.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">More time critical questions can be separated from those that are less so, enabling customer service representatives to quickly see which queries they need to deal with first.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Want to know more?&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.helpshift.com/schedule-demo/\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease-in-out; transition-property: color; letter-spacing: 0px !important; color: rgb(12, 117, 84) !important;\">Schedule a demo</a>&nbsp;to see Helpshift in action and learn how a best-in-class Help Center software could improve the experience that your business offers.</p><h3 id=\"h-why-mobile-help-centers-are-important\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 3rem; line-height: 1.25; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; font-weight: 600;\">Why Mobile Help Centers Are Important</span></h3><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Today’s customer is highly mobile, apt to need quick answers on a smartphone or tablet, and expecting they’ll be able to get them quickly. That’s why customer service today must be mobile. Help centers have to be optimized for mobile view and UX on any device.</p><h2 id=\"h-how-helpshift-supports-help-centers\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 4.2rem; line-height: 1.22; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; font-weight: 600;\">How Helpshift Supports Help Centers</span></h2><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Some customer issues will always require human assistance, so the ideal self-serve software is integrated with your live support options so that the customer’s experience is seamless. With Helpshift, customers who begin their journey using your help center may then launch a conversation with a chatbot and transition to a conversation with a real human —&nbsp;all in a seamless way so that the customer does not experience any jarring transitions, hold times, or the pain point of having to start again with a new agent.</p><p style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 1.5rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 1.8rem; line-height: 1.5; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\">Helpshift has found that brands that combine self-service tools like help centers and incorporate automated workflows powered by bots perform better than their industry peers. (View all the benchmarks in our&nbsp;<a href=\"https://go.helpshift.com/benchmark-report-q1-19.html\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"external-link\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease-in-out; transition-property: color; letter-spacing: 0px !important; color: rgb(12, 117, 84) !important;\">Digital Customer Service Benchmark Repor</a><a href=\"https://lp.helpshift.com/benchmark-report-q1-19-whitepaper\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\" class=\"external-link\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease-in-out; transition-property: color; letter-spacing: 0px !important; color: rgb(12, 117, 84) !important;\">t</a>).</p><h3 id=\"h-additional-information-about-help-centers\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; font-variant-numeric: normal; font-variant-east-asian: normal; font-stretch: normal; font-size: 3rem; line-height: 1.25; letter-spacing: 0px !important;\"><span style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; font-weight: 600;\">Additional Information About Help Centers</span></h3><ul style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 2rem 0px 0px; padding: 0px 0px 0px 2rem;\"><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; margin: 0px 0px 0.5rem 1.5rem;\">Blog post:&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.helpshift.com/blog/self-service-tools-for-your-customers/\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease-in-out; transition-property: color; letter-spacing: 0px !important; color: rgb(12, 117, 84) !important;\">Today’s Self-Service Tools Put Your Customers First</a></li><li style=\"box-sizing: inherit; letter-spacing: 0px !important; margin: 0px 0px 0.5rem 1.5rem;\">Product:<a href=\"https://www.helpshift.com/products/self-service-app/\" style=\"box-sizing: inherit; font-weight: 700; transition-duration: 0.2s; transition-timing-function: ease-in-out; transition-property: color; letter-spacing: 0px !important; color: rgb(12, 117, 84) !important;\">&nbsp;Intelligent Customer Self-Service</a></li></ul></div></div></div></section></div></main>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '2022-04-26 20:18:45', '2022-04-26 20:18:45');
