App-Landing-Pages_feature-80x43.png 80w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-150x80.png 150w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-469x250.png 469w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-650x347.png 650w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-300x160.png 300w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-160x85.png 160w\" data-sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" sizes=\"(max-width: 750px) 100vw, 750px\" srcset=\"https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature.png 750w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-80x43.png 80w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-150x80.png 150w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-469x250.png 469w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-650x347.png 650w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-300x160.png 300w, https://unbounce.com/photos/Best-App-Landing-Pages_feature-160x85.png 160w\" style=\"vertical-align: baseline; border: 0px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin-top: 0px; margin-right: auto; margin-left: auto; padding: 0px; outline: 0px; background: transparent; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); line-height: 1.56; letter-spacing: 0px; max-width: 100%; height: auto; clear: both; display: block; position: sticky; margin-bottom: 0px !important;\"></picture></div><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">Here’s a really good reason why you need an app landing page:</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">Have you looked at your iPhone’s App Store lately? How about Google Play?</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">I’ve seen&nbsp;<em style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 0.94444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6;\">landfills</em>&nbsp;with better curation.</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">With&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.statista.com/statistics/276623/number-of-apps-available-in-leading-app-stores/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">more than two million apps</a>&nbsp;available on each store, people have a much better chance of finding&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.spey.com/2017/04/05/the-odds-of-finding-a-pearl/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">a pearl in an oyster</a>&nbsp;than randomly stumbling upon your app.&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">No matter how appealing it is—no matter how entertaining or even life-changing—most people won’t discover it without a robust marketing campaign.</span></p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">(And, to paraphrase&nbsp;<a href=\"https://contently.com/2018/12/14/viral-video-strategy/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">Contently’s Bradley Little</a>, going viral is&nbsp;<em style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 0.94444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6;\">not</em>&nbsp;a strategy.)</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">The first step in marketing your iPhone or Android app is finding the right channels to promote it. Using Google Ads’ Universal App Campaigns (UAC) is a strong starting point, but many marketers get extra mileage from traditional PPC campaign, social media marketing, app cross-promotion, or even email blasts to newsletter subscribers.</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">In these cases, you’ll need a stellar landing page to overcome that hesitance we all feel about installing yet another piece of software onto our phones. For this reason,&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">ensuring a buttery-smooth post-click experience is fundamental to the app marketer’s toolbox</span>.</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">Hence this post. These are some of the&nbsp;<span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">best app landing page examples</span>&nbsp;out there, all of ’em built with Unbounce. We want to highlight how you can create a page to&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.appypie.com/how-to-promote-your-mobile-app\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">promote your own mobile app</a>&nbsp;and, as importantly, why a well-designed landing page can make all the difference. Along the way, we’ll throw in our two cents about what sets them apart.</p><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">So&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unbounce.com/landing-page-examples/app-landing-pages/#best\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">hop right into the examples below</a>, or keep reading for a handful of best practices to get you started.</p><h2 style=\"margin: 30px auto 15px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-family: &quot;Barlow Semi Condensed&quot;, sans-serif; font-size: 1.44444rem; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); line-height: 1.3; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">How to build mobile app landing pages</h2><p style=\"margin: 30px auto; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; overflow-wrap: break-word; position: sticky; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\">If you’ve created a landing page for any ol’ purpose, you may have encountered some of this advice before. But it’s worth revisiting in the context of app marketing since some elements gain increased importance when you’re hoping to score some downloads. Let’s get started:</p><ol style=\"overflow-wrap: break-word; margin: 15px auto 30px; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; padding: 0px 0px 0px 45px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 18px; color: rgb(48, 48, 48); letter-spacing: 0px; text-align: left; max-width: 750px; width: 750px;\"><li style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; position: sticky;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">Establish your conversion goal first.</span>&nbsp;As you’ll see from the examples below, an app landing page can be a lot of things. It can be a simple download page with links directly to the Android and iOS app stores. Or you might want your customers to subscribe to your service first.&nbsp;<em style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6;\">Or</em>&nbsp;they might need to purchase a physical product for the app to work. Regardless, your conversion goal will have a significant impact on your calls-to-action, your copy, and even your design. So start there.</li><li style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; position: sticky;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">Start with mobile.</span>&nbsp;If you’re like me, you default to desktop when building a new landing page. (Our builder kinda sorta encourages it, to be fair.) But since apps are designed primarily for phones, it&nbsp;<em style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-weight: inherit; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6;\">usually</em>&nbsp;makes sense to create your mobile version first. That way, you’ll better set yourself up for those visitors who’re most likely to download your app.</li><li style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; position: sticky;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">Keep their attention.</span>&nbsp;This is true of all landing pages, but app pages that encourage a direct download in particular benefit from a&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unbounce.com/conversion-centered-design/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">1:1 attention ratio</a>. So don’t give ’em the world. Instead, hit your visitors with the essential information they need to convert.</li><li style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; position: sticky;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">Show the device.</span>&nbsp;Ideally, you want to show your app running on a device that’s as similar as possible to what customers are using. Sometimes that’s an iPhone. Sometimes it’s an Android phone. It’ll differ depending on use cases, the campaign you’re running, and the kinds of customers you court.</li><li style=\"-webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px 0px 5px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px; position: sticky;\"><span style=\"font-weight: 600; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; font-size: 0.94444rem; letter-spacing: 0px; line-height: 1.6; position: sticky;\">And stay fast!</span>&nbsp;It can be tempting to take a kitchen-sink approach to your app landing page, especially if you have a lot of features to show off. But generally a slow post-click experience (think, four seconds or more) is going to generate a ton of frustration and decrease your conversions. For this reason, consider using&nbsp;<a href=\"https://unbounce.com/product/features/amp-landing-pages/\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\" target=\"_blank\" style=\"color: rgb(0, 51, 255); background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; margin: 0px; padding: 0px; font-size: 0.94444rem; vertical-align: baseline; line-height: 1.6; letter-spacing: 0px;\">the AMP-framework</a>&nbsp;to create lightning-fast pages.</li></ol></div>', 'en', '2022-04-26 20:06:12', '2022-04-26 20:06:12');
